snippet: The Food and Drug Administration expects to receive long-delayed visas soon for employees bound for its China offices, an agency official said.
abstract: Food and Drug Administration expects to receive long-delayed visas soon for employees bound for its China offices; is trying to expand its presence in China, but China has held up visas for nearly a year.
lead_paragraph: The Food and Drug Administration expects to receive long-delayed visas soon for employees bound for its China offices, an agency official said.

headline.main: F.D.A. Optimistic on Visas for China Staff
headline.print_headline: F.D.A. Optimistic on Visas for China Staff
